cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep learning approach to reduce the complexity of HEVC encoding, which involves image and video processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks (CNN) and long- and short-term memory (LSTM) network, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning, suggesting that cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also involves rate-distortion optimization (RDO), which is a common technique in information theory, suggesting that cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as well. Finally, the paper does not involve any specific hardware or system implementation, ruling out categories such as cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) or cs.OS (Operating Systems).
